COVID-19 Required Posting
09/14/20
We have been informed that two elementary students have been confirmed positive for COVID 19. The siblings were last on campus on September 8th.

CHISD will continue to monitor student temperature checks as well as practice social distancing along with the wearing of masks. We are doing our best to disinfect common areas as well as encouraging students to wash their hands thoroughly throughout the day.

post_text: CHISD has been informed as of September 6th, we have 2 staff members on the Elementary campus who have tested positive for Covid 19. Students and Parents of CHISD,
Due to the predicted impact of Hurricane Laura, CHISD will cancel all school activities and remote learning for Thursday, August 27th. At this time, we will plan to return on Friday, August, 28th if power and facilities allow.
Please look for school messages via the Remind 101 app as well as local radio and television stations.
If you do not already have the REMIND app, please follow the instructions below to be able to get district messages and updates throughout the year.

David Russell, CHISD Superintendent

The Central Heights volleyball team is selling HUGE mum flower arrangements to raise funds for our program. We have partnered with Lily Farms Nursery in Center to bring you beautiful arrangements at a great price!

Pink frenzy Purple/Orange Yellow Purple/Yellow

Color options: Cream, Orange, Purple, Red, Yellow, & Pink Frenzy

General athletic: CHISD Family!
Please see the attached letter below for our spectator protocols for the year. EVERYONE who enters a game MUST have a voucher this year. The voucher only allows you to buy a ticket at the door. There will be no walk up ticket purchases. Please observe marked rows for seats. When you do come to an event you MUST HAVE A MASK ON to enter. You will also have protocol questions to answer as you enter. We as an athletic department are doing all we can to keep things safe so we can preserve our seasons! As spectators please help us do the same!
THANK YOU!

post_text:
Dear CHISD athletes and parents,

I wanted to reach out and inform you that JH and HS summer skills will be shut down until further notice. We have had a high school athlete confirmed positive for Covid 19.. We have no way of knowing where this student was exposed to Covid or when the exposure took place. I can tell you that there were very few symptoms and the student feels great. However, as we have been doing on a daily basis, we want to do all we can to protect our students and families. If any athlete has any symptoms please get tested and continue to practice safety protocols.
text:
Dear CHISD athletes and parents,

I wanted to reach out and inform you that JH and HS summer skills will be shut down until further notice. We have had a high school athlete confirmed positive for Covid 19.. We have no way of knowing where this student was exposed to Covid or when the exposure took place. I can tell you that there were very few symptoms and the student feels great. However, as we have been doing on a daily basis, we want to do all we can to protect our students and families. If any athlete has any symptoms please get tested and continue to practice safety protocols.

Hello,

I’m excited to announce I’m leading a trip to New York next summer. This trip is going to be so much fun. Take a look at this short video that will show just how much fun we’ll have on this trip. We will be having a virtual meeting about this incredible opportunity and to be on a lookout for the invitation to the meeting.

Click here to watch the New York video.

https://vimeo.com/138640955

I can’t wait to see you and your families at our virtual meeting on Thursday, June 4th at 6 pm.

Stacey Meador
Central Heights Middle School
stacey.meador@centralhts.net

P.S.: Spread the word! Every student in Central Heights is invited so please share this with all your friends.

post_text:
CHISD will resume meal distribution beginning on Monday, April 27th. Instead of daily meals, we will be going to a twice weekly schedule that will take place on Monday’s and Wednesday’s from 11:00 am – 1:00 pm. Lunch and breakfast will be given for 2 days on Monday’s and for the remainder of the week on Wednesday’s. This will continue thru May 20th.

“CHISD reanudará la distribución de comidas a partir del lunes 27 de abril. En lugar de comidas diarias, iremos a un horario dos veces por semana que tendrá lugar los lunes y miércoles de 11:00 a.m. a 1:00 p.m. El almuerzo y el desayuno se darán durante 2 días los lunes y el resto de la semana los miércoles. Esto continuará hasta el 20 de mayo.”

post_text:
March 30, 2020
Dear Central Heights ISD Family,
After visiting with other Nacogdoches County Superintendents over the weekend, CHISD has decided to extend its closure thru April 17th.
Both the city and county of Nacogdoches have declared a " stay home " order starting at noon today. I have communicated with Greg Sowell (County Judge) and this does not pertain to the delivery of instructional materials and student meals. We will continue to offer instruction online as well as packet pickups following the schedule that we started on March 23rd and we will also continue to offer meals to students 18 and under each day Monday-Friday.
An update pertaining to information regarding Transfer Applications will be posted on the CHISD website beginning on April 6th. Current transfers should be receiving a letter in the mail soon and we are asking that everything is returned by mail during the school closure.
We appreciate your patience during this time.

David Russell
CHISD Superintendent

Parents and Families—this year’s Boosterthon Fun Run is "Runnin with the Devils!" It’s a two-week program that kicks off on March 18, 2020. Families will gather pledges for every lap your student runs (30-35 laps) at the Runnin with the Devils Fun Run, which will happen on March 27, 2020. This year our goal is to raise $14,000, and we need your help! We’ve asked the experts at Booster to power our fundraiser to make it easier, more profitable, and more fun.

Students will also experience an amazing character theme, MINDSPARK: WILD WEST! Booster’s most exciting theme yet combines S.T.E.A.M. skills (Science, Technology, Engineering, Arts, and Math) with character-building. While they're teaming up with the MindSpark Kids to save Dr. Shock, our students will learn five character traits that will help strengthen themselves and our world.

All families are invited to come out and cheer on our students at the Runnin with the Devils Fun Run. Thanks so much for your support!--

Jana Muckleroy

Fourteen high school and two middle school band members traveled to SFA on Saturday for the UIL Solo & Ensemble Contest. Adam Engstrom and Abigail Ferretiz performed solos and earned 2nd divisions. A flute trio with Abigail, Diana Lobato, and Madeleine Francesca Mullin (7th) also earned the 2nd division. These students performed very difficult pieces and I am very proud of them!

Jordan Engstrom earned a 1st division on her clarinet solo. A clarinet quartet with Jordan, Jaden Lott, Daisy Attaway, and Jack Goranson earned a 1st division as well and will advance to the state contest in May.

Central Heights ISD is asking you to join us in the Pop Tab Collection Program for the Ronald McDonald House of Ft. Worth, Texas.

Little things can make a big difference.

Please help us support one of our students by collecting the little tabs you pull to open soda, soup or other aluminum cans. The funds generated from recycling these aluminum gems help offset the Ronald McDonald House's expenses.

You may drop off the tabs at the Elementary, Middle School, High School, or the Administration office.

Thank you so much for helping us help others!

Central Heights ISD is announcing the following openings

District Curriculum Coach / GT Coordinator (207- 226 Days) – As the District Curriculum Coach, you will be expected to work with teachers (PK-12) in observing teachers' instruction, analyzing test data, assessing education standards, reviewing textbooks, recommending instructional techniques, assisting administration in arranging professional development workshops, developing assessments, and responding to teachers' questions.

As the Gifted and Talented Coordinator, you will coordinate the campus programs for gifted and talented students. Collaborate with district staff and outside personnel to provide educational opportunities for gifted and talented students.

Employment applications can be downloaded at centralhts.org Resumes and applications can be sent via e-mail to david.russell@centralhts.net Mailings should be addressed to CHISD Attn: David Russell, 10317 U.S. Hwy 259 North Nacogdoches, Tx. 75965

post_text:
Red Ribbon Week 2019
October 28-November 1, 2019

Welcome to Red Ribbon Week 2019. Red Ribbon Week is October 28-November 1, 2019. You are invited to participate in a week of spirit to celebrate our choice to be drug-free.

Monday, October 28-Friends stick together to fight drugs. Dress like a friend. Twin, Triplet, Quadruplet etc.

Tuesday, October 29-Follow your dreams, don't do drugs. Pajama day.

Wednesday, October 30-Wear Red to support Red Ribbon Week.

Thursday, October 31-Sock it to drugs. Crazy sock day.

Friday, November 1, 2019-Be on a Drug Free Team. Wear your Central Heights Blue or your favorite team shirt.

Looking for a way to support a great organization and eat some good BBQ? Please continue reading...

We just wanted to remind everyone that the Central Heights-Appleby Fire Dept BBQ is coming up Sunday, Oct 6th at the Central Heights Elementary school cafeteria and to once again ask for your help in making desserts. If you are willing to make a dessert please let us know by email to CHAVFD@yahoo.com or russell84_2002@yahoo.com. We will be at the school on Saturday the 5th, from 8am-12pm if you would like to drop it off then or any time on Sunday morning. Some of you may also receive a duplicating phone call later in the week about this and I apologize for any inconvenience this may cause. Thank You for your continued support.

post_text: We have some exciting changes to our Blue Devil Sports Photography this year! Creative Photography will provide all our player and team photos for all sports. Clay Bostian and Trecia Johnson have teamed up to photograph all of our athletes. Clay and Trecia are both professional photographers with more than 20 years of experience; and they are both parents of Blue Devils! Expect a high level of quality and creativity in our sports portraits this year as well as some impressive Spirit Banners of our athletes on display in our school. Each sport will have exclusive Picture Days over the next several weeks, so watch for Sports Package order forms to be sent home with your child. Orders may also be pre-paid online at www.creativephotographynac.hhimagehost.com Volleyball Picture Day is Thursday, Sept. 19

post_text: CHHS students found success at the 2019 State Academic Meet at the University of Texas last Friday. Senior Kennedy Grigsby placed 3rd in Headline Writing and 6th in Copy Editing. Sophomore Kylie Gast placed 5th in Ready Writing. Other state qualifiers were senior Catherine Meisenheimer, Literary Criticism, and junior Ashlyn Jones, News Writing. Senior Cameron Castilaw was an alternate for Current Issues & Events and junior Caitlyn Shrewsbury was an alternate for Ready Writing.

Blue Devils are reaching out to help the people of the Alto community.
Central Heights High School Student Council is sponsoring a Storm Relief Drive this Monday, April 15 and Tuesday, April 16 for the Alto community. We will be accepting donations and supplies at all three campuses all day Monday, Tuesday, and Wednesday morning. Drop-off points are the HS Office, MS office, and the ELEM office. Donations will be used to purchase additional supplies to be taken to Alto with the rest of the supplies Wednesday afternoon.
A list of what supplies that are needed is attached to this message and Facebook post.
For more information, please contact the CHHS office at 936-552-3408.

post_text: Our theatre students participated in the UIL One-Act Play 3A district 21 competition on March 5th and received 1st place! They won Outstanding Tech Crew and also brought home many individual awards. Maya Delaguila received Best Actress, Gabby Carney received Honor Tech Crew, David Smith and Caitlyn Shrewsbury received All-Star Cast, and Rebecca Martin received Honorable Mention All-Star Cast. We are so proud of all they have achieved and will be cheering them on as they compete at the bi-district contest on March 23rd.

post_text:
Central Heights will host a Community Conversation Cafe' on February 28th at 6:30 pm in the High School Library. This is a conversation to identify problems or concerns within the community and work toward solutions. Community members are invited.

Nacogdoches County Community Collaborative is working to increase the quality of care and well being of residents in Nacogdoches County by listening to the voice of the community. They are a group made up of community members, city, county and school officials, law enforcement, business leaders, service organizations and individuals from all communities in Nacogdoches County. This work will include everyone in our community and all are welcome.
